- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and conversational data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for identifying context dependent messages. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed method uses a Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) network for classification. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the study involves analyzing social conversation data crawled from the web. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with identifying relevant messages based on their linguistic context.
